   "source": [
    "The sequential baseline runs single-threaded scikit-learn DBSCAN entirely on the driver. To minimise driver memory, only `trajectory_id`, `latitude`, and `longitude` are loaded from parquet. Duplicate coordinate pairs are removed before clustering: since DBSCAN is purely coordinate-based, duplicate (lat, lon) pairs would receive identical labels. Labels are assigned to unique coordinates and mapped back to all original rows via a coordinate merge, preserving the full row count for downstream comparisons and ARI/NMI evaluation.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key parameters:** `eps=0.0045`, `min_samples=5`, `n_jobs=1` (single-threaded, matching the distributed workers), `algorithm='ball_tree'` for efficient neighbourhood queries."
   ]
